Principal Deputy Press Secretary Sarah Huckabee Sanders appeared on ABC's This Week and made several statements. She addressed the ongoing controversy surrounding the Trump administration's alleged ties to Russia, stating that the FBI has already deemed the story as false. Sanders emphasized that the American people deserve to know the truth and that it is time to move on and focus on issues that matter to them, such as the economy, education, border security, and national security. She also discussed the need to repeal and replace Obamacare, stating that even Democrats admit it is not sustainable. Finally, Sanders defended President Trump's decision to skip the White House Correspondents' Dinner, stating that he was elected to speak directly to the American people and will prioritize issues that can better the country.